    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-20T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-20T06:00:00-05:00" n="662"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d662">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.6363 Standard Oil Co./38: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-20T11:00:00+00:00"
                            >February 20, 1934—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 20—7:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>70. Department’s 50, February 19, 6 p.m.<note n="19" xml:id="d662fn19">Not
                        printed.</note> Saudi Arabian Minister conveys his Government’s
                    authorization for the use of aeroplane for geological purposes and states that
                    details regulating this flight have been completed by the Saudi Arabian
                    Government and the representatives of the California-Arabian Standard Oil
                    Company there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
